
⚙️ Create Lambda Function for Agent Tools

In this step, we create the AWS Lambda function that will:

Discover unused or chargeable AWS resources

Perform safe deletion of selected resources

Act as the execution layer for the Bedrock Agent



🎯 Purpose of Lambda

This function is used by the Bedrock Agent Action Group to:

Execute AWS API operations

Return results back to the AI agent

Enable real-time infrastructure analysis and actions



🪜 Step-by-Step: Create Lambda Function

🪜 Step 1: Open AWS Lambda Console

Navigate to: AWS Lambda → Functions

Click Create function



🪜 Step 2: Configure Basic Settings

Select: Author from scratch

Fill the following details:

Function Name:
BedrockCostAgentTools

Runtime:
Python 3.12

Architecture:
x86_64



🪜 Step 3: Configure Execution Role

Expand Change default execution role

Select: Use an existing role

Choose:

BedrockCostAgentLambdaRole

👉 This allows Lambda to interact with AWS services securely



🪜 Step 4: Create Function

Click Create function



💻 Step 5: Add Lambda Code
🪜 Step 5.1: Open Code Editor

Go to Code → lambda_function.py

Remove the default code

🪜 Step 5.2: Add Your Logic

#copy and Paste from lambda code python  into lambda_function.py



🪜 Step 5.3: Deploy Code

Click Deploy



⚙️ Step 6: Configure Lambda Settings
🪜 Step 6.1: Open Configuration

Go to Configuration → General configuration

Click Edit



🪜 Step 6.2: Update Settings

Memory: 512 MB

Timeout: 30 seconds

👉 These settings ensure:

Enough performance for scanning resources

No timeout during execution

Click Save



🧪 Step 7: Test Lambda Function

Go to Test tab

Create a test event

Click Test



✅ Expected Result:

Function executes successfully

Logs visible in CloudWatch



✅ Final Result

Your Lambda function is now:

✅ Successfully created

✅ Connected with IAM Role

✅ Ready to be used by Bedrock Agent



🧠 Architecture Integration
User → Bedrock Agent → Lambda → AWS Services

Agent decides the action

Lambda executes it

AWS services return results

🔥 Key Takeaway

This Lambda function is the execution engine of your AI system —

it turns intelligent decisions into real AWS actions 🚀
